data.name: textBox9.Text
data.value: Holding Shift will multiply the note duration by 1.5, making it a dotted note. For example, holding shift on a quarter note will make it a dotted quarter, which is basically a quarter note and an eighth note.

data.name: textBox8.Text
data.value: Pressing the L key will bring up all the available durations based off the selected time signature. Once the menu is up, click on any note duration to have that as your selected duration. Pressing TAB will also loop through them in order.

data.name: textBox3.Text
data.value: Use the numeric to change how many staves there are. Use the top 4 drop down menus to change what Clef you use on each stave you created. The bottom 4 dropdown menus are for waveforms, which change the sound of the notes. Use the buttons on the right to choose whether you have a bracket, brace, or none. This shows the grouping of an instrument.

data.name: textBox7.Text
data.value: In order to add notes to the song, simply type the notes from the keyboard. The note position on the staff could change if different cleffs were selected to work from, but the notes will stay the same from the keyboard. R is for a rest.

data.name: textBox13.Text
data.value: Once a note has been put into the song, there is a way to change that note without deleting it and retyping it. Click on the note that needs to be changed and type the new note. It will replace the highlighted note with the note that was typed.
